# Project Architecture

This is a **Distributed k-Anonymity** system for medical research data sharing (Project #102).

## System Structure

```
distributed-k-anonymity/
├── coordinator/       # Main coordinator (port 3000)
│   ├── index.js       # Express server, orchestrates the algorithm
│   └── kanonymity.js  # k-anonymity algorithm (generalization + suppression)
├── node-a/           # Site A — TP.HCM (port 3001), ZipCode 7xxxx
│   ├── index.js       # Express server
│   ├── database.js    # SQLite (sql.js) operations
│   └── site_a.db     # Auto-created on first run
├── node-b/           # Site B — Hanoi (port 3002), ZipCode 1xxxx
│   ├── index.js       # Express server
│   ├── database.js    # SQLite (sql.js) operations
│   └── site_b.db     # Auto-created on first run
├── scripts/
│   └── generate-data.js  # Synthetic dataset generation
└── package.json
```

## Communication Pattern

- **Coordinator** (port 3000) initiates requests
- **Node A** (port 3001) and **Node B** (port 3002) respond to GET requests
- All communication is HTTP REST (JSON)
- Coordinator fetches data from all nodes, then runs the k-anonymity algorithm

## Key Design Decisions

- **SQLite via sql.js** (WASM) — avoids native compilation issues on Windows
- **Horizontal fragmentation** by ZipCode prefix (7xxxx vs 1xxxx)
- **Multi-dimensional generalization**: Age (4 levels) + ZipCode (5 levels)
- **No suppression by default** — algorithm tries generalization first, suppression only when necessary

## Always Apply

When modifying this project:
- Keep all 3 servers running simultaneously for full system tests
- After modifying coordinator/kanonymity.js, restart the coordinator server
- After modifying scripts/generate-data.js, run `npm run generate` then restart all servers
- Test `/run` endpoint after any algorithm change
- Never commit `*.db` files
